info.headline: High Wind Warning issued May 11 at 5:04PM CDT until May 11 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM CDT THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Damaging winds to 70 MPH. * WHERE...Northern Aitkin, South Aitkin and Carlton and South St. Louis Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Fond du Lac Band and the Mille Lacs Band, East Lake and, Big Sandy Lake areas. * WHEN...Until 7 PM CDT this evening. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Aitkin County sheriff reported extensive wind damage in parts of Aitkin early this evening. They had numerous trees blown down and metal roofs ripped off structures. These winds were associated with a decaying area of showers and not with thunderstorms.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
